Sentencas: The effects of anode microstructure on mechanical and electrochemical properties were investigated for anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Effects of Anode Microstructure on Mechanical and Electrochemical Properties for Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The anode microstructures can be varied by the change in pore formers.
Titulo: Effects of Anode Microstructure on Mechanical and Electrochemical Properties for Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: For example, the acrylic resin pore former was burnt more rapidly at lower temperature than the graphite pore former during sintering.
Titulo: Effects of Anode Microstructure on Mechanical and Electrochemical Properties for Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The acrylic resin pore former can introduce macropores with a diameter of several micrometers in nickel-yttria-stabilized zirconia (Ni-YSZ) anode.
Titulo: Effects of Anode Microstructure on Mechanical and Electrochemical Properties for Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The walls of the macropores were packed with the nickel and YSZ particles.
Titulo: Effects of Anode Microstructure on Mechanical and Electrochemical Properties for Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Although the Ni-YSZ anode microtube using the 10wt% acrylic resin pore former was compatible with high porosity and mechanical strength, the maximum fuel utilization was limited to 72%.
Titulo: Effects of Anode Microstructure on Mechanical and Electrochemical Properties for Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: On the other hand, the graphite pore former can produce a relatively uniform distribution of micropores with a diameter of several hundred nanometers.
Titulo: Effects of Anode Microstructure on Mechanical and Electrochemical Properties for Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The mechanical strength was reduced with a rise in porosity for the Ni-YSZ microtube using the graphite pore former in comparison with the acrylic resin.
Titulo: Effects of Anode Microstructure on Mechanical and Electrochemical Properties for Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, a high fuel utilization of 93% was realized for the microtubular SOFCs using the 10wt% graphite pore former in spite of lower porosity than the acrylic resin.
Titulo: Effects of Anode Microstructure on Mechanical and Electrochemical Properties for Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The selection of a pore former is important to obtain higher power generation efficiency for anode-supported microtubular SOFCs.
Titulo: Effects of Anode Microstructure on Mechanical and Electrochemical Properties for Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
